The new head of staff of Trump plans to limit the flow of information to the president.
Others tried to do so and were defeated.
Maybe John F. Kelly can really do it.
Then he'll be the first.
Politico reports that the new White House Chief of Staff is planning to limit the flow of information to President Trump, including news reports from the media, in the hope of keeping the Chief calm.
