"At a meeting held by the new White House Chief of Staff, John F. Kelly, with the management of the office on his first working day, he identified the main problem in the White House under President Donald Trump, which he hopes to solve: poor channels of information to the President."
Kelly told the staff that information should go through him - paper or briefing - because the president would be better at making decisions if he got the right information.
Kelly's diagnosis is perfectly correct, but others have already failed in trying to control Trump by tracking his information.
President Trump's relationship with television began decades ago, and now that he's in the White House, his habit of watching TV is still strong.
