Bruins' team has to work longer because the National Student Sports Association canceled practice twice a day.
Time is approaching 11:00 p.m.; a crowd of football players from the University of California in Los Angeles is delayed to chat on one side of the team's new campus training fields.
Some of them pulled their T-shirts, exposed their backs, glittering from sweat after a busy first day of sports camp.
For many players in the team, these idle minutes are a break in the middle of the day.
