The fact that the National Student Sports Association cancelled training twice a day, which was designed to reduce the burden on the players, actually extended their working hours – at least until the end of the exams on Friday.
Therefore, the first three training sessions of the California University team in Los Angeles were scheduled to begin at 7:15 p.m., so that they could fit in with an already tight schedule of players.
