I think that when we get to Saturday and we have more time, it'll be really great."
When the camp is over, the University of California in Los Angeles will close the training; this is not an easy task, as its fields are in direct view from the adjacent parking lot and from the nearby Laskin Center, a expensive hotel that has already been bombed by footballs that have crossed the security grid behind the gates.
Bruins players should occupy a hotel starting this weekend, but Maura admits that when rooms are available during the season, there may be a problem.
"We'll have security," Maura said.
"It's a serious problem, and I don't exaggerate the danger by suggesting that someone can rent a room, sit there and record the training in a video.
If you have a video of training, it's very serious.
